                <p class="text-justify">Bek Air was founded as Berkut Air in 1999 as a business jet operator in Kazakhstan and initiated domestic scheduled services. The airline was rebranded to Bek Air in 2011 after investing KZT10 million (US$30,000) a month to reconstruct the airport's runway, which was in poor condition. Bek Air offers services to Aktau, Aktobe, Almaty, Atyrau, Kyzylorda, Nur-Sultan, Oral, Pavlodar, and Shymkent.  </p>
