                <h2>Cancellation policy</h2>
                <p class="text-justify">With reference to Bek Air cancellation policy, you can cancel a flight booked on Bek Air within 24 hours of the purchase. If the booking was made a week or more prior to the departure date of your flight, you can receive full refund. </p>
                <p class="text-justify">If you cancel the flight a few hours before the departure and the flight was booked not more than a week before then you will have to pay the cancellation fee depending upon the fare rules. </p>
                <h3>Refund policy </h3>
                <p class="text-justify">You will receive refund only for the eligible <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/">flight tickets</a> that were canceled within the active span of time. If the airline cancels your flight due to any unavoidable reasons, then they will provide you compensation to book the next subsequent Bek Air flight. In such a situation, you can easily cancel your flight and get a refund on Bek Air. </p>
                <h4>Frequently asked question</h4>
                <h3 class="text-justify">How to cancel a flight ticket with Bek Air? </h3>
                <p class="text-justify">You can call the Bek Air customer care office and inform them about the cancellation. You may also contact your kiosk to help you through the cancellation process. Apart from this, you may also visit the official website of the airlines and cancel your flight ticket. </p>
                <h3 class="text-justify">When can I make the request for the refund? By when can I expect it? </h3>
                <p class="text-justify">You can make a request for the refund online by filling the refund request form at Bek Air official site. The refund request takes time to be processed and can be granted within 7 to 10 working days. </p>
                <h3 class="text-justify">Can I ask for compensation if my flight gets delayed by 2 hours? </h3>
                <p class="text-justify">If your replacement flight delays your arrival by 2 or more hours or your flight was canceled less than 14 days before departure, you are eligible to get compensation. </p>
